# FILE ORGANIZATION RULES

ALL new files MUST be placed in the correct directory:

| Directory | Contents |
|-----------|----------|
| `agents/` | Agent files (.py) -- MUST use subdirectories (Main/, Support/, Core/, Adapters/, Services/, Utils/) |
| `config/` | Configuration files (.json, .yaml, .properties, specs) |
| `docs/` | Documentation files (.md, .txt, .rst) |
| `examples/` | Example and utility scripts (.py) |
| `User story/` | User stories and flow files (.txt, .drawio, .md) -- MANDATORY for ALL story/flow files |
| `reports/YYYY-MM-DD/` | Reports (.md) -- ALWAYS use current date dynamically |
| `test_cases/` | Test cases -- Objects/ (by entity) and Flows/ (by flow) as siblings. See test_cases_structure.mdc |
| `postman/` | Postman collections |
| `Phoenix/` | Phoenix Java project files (READ-ONLY for AI) |

- Reports MUST be in `Cursor-Project/reports/YYYY-MM-DD/` (project root, not workspace root)
- User stories MUST be in `User story/` directory and written in English
- NEVER place files directly in workspace root when a directory exists for that type
